item.title: Global Coalition of Legislators Faces Challenges Countering China
item.description: The formation of an unusual coalition of developed-world lawmakers shows how misgivings over Beijing’s recent assertiveness have rippled across the globe

item.title: Syria's Assad Faces Growing Pressure From the Street Over Slumping Economy
item.description: Demonstrations are rarely seen in government-controlled areas, but they are testing the Syrian leader’s authority as he attempts to consolidate power after nine years of conflict.

item.title: Hong Kong Police Move to Stall Protest Revival
item.description: Police in riot gear fanned out across Hong Kong in large numbers on Friday in a show of force aimed at quashing possible unrest.

item.title: On East Africa's Borders, Vast Jams as Truckers Are Tested for Covid-19
item.description: Journeys that normally take a week now take up to a month as food supplies and other shipments are trapped in traffic jams up to 50 miles long, disrupting economies and frustrating drivers.

item.title: Differences Between New Coronavirus and SARS Show Why Quick Economic Recovery Is Unlikely
item.description: The new coronavirus’s stealthily, swift and global spread means nations must wait on their trading, travel and business partners for a recovery.
